race.comment: CAPTAIN EAGLE (2) comes here off a last start 3L defeat over 1660m at Doomben. Wasn't entirely happy on the heavy track and was even better placing at the Sunshine Coast the one before over a mile. Huxtable is a positive jockey booking and he looks to have an edge on most of these. BAVARIAN LADY (4) did a big job winning a 60 this track/trip job by 3L, and she keeps improving. Has the inside gate and Wiggins and rates a threat. SOMETHING FORJO (7) turned in a decent effort last start when placing over 1625m at Toowoomba. Going well enough to consider. SECURITY ADVISOR (5) returned to the winners' circle after a long while in the wilderness last time out over 1900m at this track, scoring by 0.9 lengths. Can go on with it.
